# learn-python-
python for beginners 
Python is a high-level programming language created by Guido van Rossum in 1991. 
It is designed to be easy to read, write, and understand, making it popular among both beginners and experienced developers.
Its syntax is simple and often resembles plain English, which reduces the learning curve significantly.
It is used for:
  1)web development (server-side),
  2)software development,
  3)mathematics,
  4)system scripting. etc 
